result.execSummary:
The defendant Travis Maurice Newell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(>3-10g) [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime, Penalties for Felonies-Class "E" Felony], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)2.
  • Possession of Methamphetamine [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "I" Felony], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Court questions DE. Court finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights to testify. Court has developed jury instructions, Atty's have requested certain instructions. Atty Dunlap is requesting 780 intrapment for Count 2. ADA Hahn responds. Court reviews jury instructions. Atty. Dunlap argues. ADA Hahn argues. Atty. Dunlap responds. Court will insert 780 relative to Count 2. ADA Hahn questions the court as to closings. Court will permit the jury to view exhibits during closings. Evidence is closed. Recess at 8:58. Court reviews again with DE his right to testify. It is DE decision not to testify. Case called at 9:18 in the presence of the jury. Court gives jury instructions 9:19. Closing arguments by ADA Hahn at 9:46. Closing arguments by Atty. Dunlap 10:20. Rebuttal by ADA Hahn 10:47. Court supplements instruction of credibility as a Jury Instruction. Oath to Bailiff at 10:59. Jury out to deliberate at 11:03. Adjourn at  Bond continues in form and amount. Case recalled at 12:57 with a verdict. 

We, the jury, duly impaneled, as and for our verdict in the above captioned matter, find the Defendant, Travis M. Newell, guilty of Delivery of Methamphetamine- As a Party to the Crime as charged in the first count of the information.  Was the amount of methamphetamine more than 3 grams? Answer: Yes

We the jury, duly impaneled, as and for our verdict in the above captioned matterm find the Defendant, Travis M. Newell, guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine as charged in the second count of the information.
